Outcome2: Carefully consider his options and discuss it with his family

QuestionLabel: Alan helps Trudy, a peer he works with occasionally, with a difficult task. Trudy complains that Alan's work isn't very good, and Alan responds that Trudy should be grateful he is doing her a favor. They argue. What action would be the most effective for Alan?

CorrectOutcomeLabel: Diffuse the argument by asking for advice

QuestionLabel: Surbhi starts a new job where he doesn't know anyone and finds that no one is particularly friendly. What action would be the most effective for Surbhi?
Outcome1: Make an effort to talk to people and be friendly himself
Outcome2: Concentrate on doing his work well at the new job

QuestionLabel: Darla is nervous about presenting her work to a group of seniors who might not understand it, as they don't know much about her area. What action would be the most effective for Darla?

Outcome2: Work on her presentation, simplifying the explanations
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Work on her presentation, simplifying the explanations

QuestionLabel: Andre moves away from the city his friends and family are in. He finds his friends make less effort to keep in contact than he thought they would. What action would be the most effective for Andre?
Outcome1: He should make the effort to contact them, but also try to meet people in his new city
Outcome2: Try to adjust to life in the new city by joining clubs and activities there
CorrectOutcomeLabel: He should make the effort to contact them, but also try to meet people in his new city

QuestionLabel: Helga's team has been performing very well. They receive poor-quality work from another team that they must incorporate into their own project. What action would be the most effective for Helga?
Outcome1: Tell the other team they must re-do their work
Outcome2: Tell the project manager about the situation
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Tell the project manager about the situation

QuestionLabel: Clayton has been overseas for a long time and returns to visit his family. So much has changed that Clayton feels left out. What action would be the most effective for Clayton?
Outcome1: Tell his family he feels left out
Outcome2: Spend time listening and getting involved again
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Spend time listening and getting involved again

QuestionLabel: Katerina takes a long time to set the DVD timer. With the family watching, her sister says “You idiot, you're doing it all wrong, can't you work the video?” Katerina is quite close to her sister and family. What action would be the most effective for Katerina?
Outcome1: Get her sister to help or to do it
Outcome2: Ignore her sister and keep at the task
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Get her sister to help or to do it

QuestionLabel: Benjiro's parents are in their late 80s and living interstate in a house by themselves. He is worried that they need some help but they angrily deny it any time he brings up the subject. What action would be the most effective for Benjiro?
Outcome1: Visit frequently and get others to check on them
Outcome2: Keep telling his parents his concerns, stressing their importance
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Visit frequently and get others to check on them

QuestionLabel: Max prides himself on his work being of the highest quality. On a joint project, other people do a lousy job, assuming that Max will fix their mistakes. What action would be the most effective for Max?
Outcome1: Confront the others, and tell them they must fix their mistakes
Outcome2: Tell the project manager about the situation
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Confront the others, and tell them they must fix their mistakes

QuestionLabel: Daniel has been accepted for a prestigious position in a different country from his family, who he is close to. He and his wife decide it is worth relocating. What action would be the most effective for Daniel?
Outcome1: Think about the great opportunities this change offers
Outcome2: Set up a system for staying in touch, like weekly phone calls or emails
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Set up a system for staying in touch, like weekly phone calls or emails

QuestionLabel: A junior employee making routine adjustments to some of Teo's equipment accuses Teo of causing the equipment malfunction. What action would be the most effective for Teo?
Outcome1: Ignore the accusation, it is not important
Outcome2: Explain that malfunctions were not his fault
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Explain that malfunctions were not his fault

QuestionLabel: Mei Ling answers the phone and hears that close relatives are in hospital critically ill. What action would be the most effective for Mei Ling?
Outcome1: Speak to other family to calm herself and find out what is happening, then visit the hospital
Outcome2: Let herself cry and express emotion for as long as she feels like
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Speak to other family to calm herself and find out what is happening, then visit the hospital

QuestionLabel: The woman who relieves Celia at the end of her shift is twenty minutes late without excuse or apology. What action would be the most effective for Celia?
Outcome1: Tell her that this is unacceptable
Outcome2: Ask for an explanation of her lateness
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Ask for an explanation of her lateness

QuestionLabel: Upon entering full-time study, Vincent cannot afford the time or money he used to spend on water-polo training, which he was quite good at. Although he enjoys full-time study, he misses training. What action would be the most effective for Vincent?
Outcome1: See if there is a local league or a less expensive and less time-consuming sport
Outcome2: Find out about sporting scholarships or bursaries
CorrectOutcomeLabel: See if there is a local league or a less expensive and less time-consuming sport

QuestionLabel: Evan's housemate cooked food late at night and left a huge mess in the kitchen that Evan discovered at breakfast. What action would be the most effective for Evan?
Outcome1: Tell his housemate to clean up the mess
Outcome2: Ask his housemate that this not happen again
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Ask his housemate that this not happen again

QuestionLabel: Greg has just gone back to university after a lapse of several years. He is surrounded by younger students who seem very confident about their ability and he is unsure whether he can compete with them. What action would be the most effective for Greg?
Outcome1: Study hard and attend all lectures
Outcome2: Talk to others in his situation
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Talk to others in his situation

QuestionLabel: Gloria's housemates never buy essential non-food items when they are running low, relying on Gloria to buy them, which she resents. They know each other reasonably well, but have not yet discussed financial issues. What action would be the most effective for Gloria?
Outcome1: Tell her housemates she has a problem with this
Outcome2: Introduce a new system for grocery shopping and sharing costs
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Tell her housemates she has a problem with this

QuestionLabel: Shona has not spoken to her nephew for months, whereas when he was younger they were very close. She rings him but he can only talk for five minutes. What action would be the most effective for Shona?
Outcome1: Understand that relationships change, but keep calling him from time to time
Outcome2: Make plans to drop by and visit him in person and have a good chat
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Understand that relationships change, but keep calling him from time to time

QuestionLabel: Moshe finds out that some members of his social sports team have been saying that he is not a very good player. What action would be the most effective for Moshe?
Outcome1: Although he may be bad at sport, remember he is good at other things
Outcome2: Do some extra training to try and improve
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Do some extra training to try and improve

QuestionLabel: Joel has always dealt with one particular client but on a very complex job his boss gives the task to a co-worker instead. Joel wonders whether his boss thinks he can't handle the important jobs. What action would be the most effective for Joel?
Outcome1: Do good work so that he will be given the complex tasks in future
Outcome2: Ask his boss why the co-worker was given the job
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Ask his boss why the co-worker was given the job

QuestionLabel: Hasina is overseas when she finds out that her father has passed away from an illness he has had for years. What action would be the most effective for Hasina?
Outcome1: Think deeply about the more profound meaning of this loss
Outcome2: Contact her close relatives for information and support
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Contact her close relatives for information and support

QuestionLabel: Mina and her sister-in-law normally get along quite well, and the sister-in-law regularly baby-sits for her for a small fee. Lately she has also been cleaning away cobwebs, commenting on the mess, which Mina finds insulting. What action would be the most effective for Mina?
Outcome1: Tell her sister-in-law these comments upset her
Outcome2: Tell her only to baby-sit, not to clean
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Tell her sister-in-law these comments upset her

QuestionLabel: Billy is nervous about acting a scene when there are a lot of very experienced actors in the crowd. What action would be the most effective for Billy?
Outcome1: Use some acting techniques to clam his nerves
Outcome2: Believe in himself and know it will be fine
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Use some acting techniques to calm his nerves

QuestionLabel: Juno is fairly sure his company is going down and his job is under threat. It is a large company and nothing official has been said. What action would be the most effective for Juno?
Outcome1: Think of these events as an opportunity for a new start
Outcome2: Find out what is happening and discuss his concerns with his family
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Find out what is happening and discuss his concerns with his family

QuestionLabel: Mallory moves from a small company to a very large one, where there is little personal contact, which she misses. What action would be the most effective for Mallory?
Outcome1: Concentrate on her outside-work friends and colleagues from previous jobs
Outcome2: Talk to her workmates, try to create social contacts and make friends
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Talk to her workmates, try to create social contacts and make friends

QuestionLabel: A demanding client takes up a lot of Jill's time and then asks to speak to Jill's boss about her performance. Although Jill's boss assures her that her performance is fine, Jill feels upset. What action would be the most effective for Jill?
Outcome1: Think that she has been successful in the past and this client being difficult is not her fault
Outcome2: Calm down by taking deep breaths or going for a short walk
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Think that she has been successful in the past and this client being difficult is not her fault

QuestionLabel: Blair and Flynn usually go to a cafe after the working week and chat about what's going on in the company. After Blair's job is moved to a different section in the company, he stops coming to the cafe. Flynn misses these Friday talks. What action would be the most effective for Flynn?
Outcome1: Go to the cafe or socialize with other workers
Outcome2: Invite Blair again, maybe rescheduling for another time
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Invite Blair again, maybe rescheduling for another time

QuestionLabel: Jerry has had several short-term jobs in the same industry, but is excited about starting a job in a different industry. His father casually remarks that he will probably last six months. What action would be the most effective for Jerry?
Outcome1: Tell his father he is completely wrong
Outcome2: Prove him wrong by working hard to succeed at the new job
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Prove him wrong by working hard to succeed at the new job

QuestionLabel: Michelle's friend Dara is moving overseas to live with her partner. They have been good friends for many years and Dara is unlikely to come back. What action would be the most effective for Michelle?
Outcome1: Make sure she keeps in contact through email, phone or letter writing
Outcome2: Spend time with other friends, keeping herself busy
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Make sure she keeps in contact through email, phone or letter writing

QuestionLabel: Dorian needs to have some prostate surgery and is quite scared about the process. He has heard that it is quite painful. What action would be the most effective for Dorian?
Outcome1: Talk to his doctor about what will happen
Outcome2: Keep busy in the meantime so he doesn't think about the impending surgery
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Talk to his doctor about what will happen

QuestionLabel: Hannah's access to essential resources has been delayed and her work is way behind schedule. Her progress report makes no mention of the lack of resources. What action would be the most effective for Hannah?
Outcome1: Document the lack of resources in her progress report
Outcome2: Explain the lack of resources to her boss or to management
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Document the lack of resources in her progress report

QuestionLabel: Jill is given an official warning for entering a restricted area. She was never informed that the area was restricted and will lose her job if she gets two more warnings, which she thinks is unfair. What action would be the most effective for Jill?

Outcome2: Accept the warning and be careful not to go in restricted areas from now on
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Explain that she didn't know it was restricted

CorrectOutcomeLabel: Ask management if an exception can be made

Outcome1: Realize that children develop at different rates
Outcome2: Talk to a doctor about what the normal rates of development are
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Talk to a doctor about what the normal rates of development are

QuestionLabel: Jumah has been working at a new job part-time while he studies. His shift times for the week are changed at the last minute, without consulting him. What action would be the most effective for Jumah?
Outcome1: Find out if there is some reasonable explanation for the shift changes
Outcome2: Tell the manager in charge of shifts that he is not happy about it
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Find out if there is some reasonable explanation for the shift changes

QuestionLabel: Jacob is having a large family gathering to celebrate him moving into his new home. He wants the day to go smoothly and is a little nervous about it. What action would be the most effective for Jacob?

Outcome2: Prepare ahead of time so he has everything he needs available
CorrectOutcomeLabel: Prepare ahead of time so he has everything he needs available

Outcome2: Understand that people change, so move on, but remember the good times
